739. Daily Temperatures
Problem

Given an array temperatures, return an array answer such that:

answer[i] = number of days you have to wait after the iᵗʰ day to get a warmer temperature.
If there is no future warmer day, return 0.
Example 1
Input:
temperatures = [73,74,75,71,69,72,76,73]

Output:
[1,1,4,2,1,1,0,0]
Example 2
Input:
temperatures = [30,40,50,60]

Output:
[1,1,1,0]
Example 3
Input:
temperatures = [30,60,90]

Output:
[1,1,0]
Key Observation

For every temperature, find the next warmer temperature on the right.

This is exactly a Next Greater Element problem.

Possible approaches:

Brute Force
Better (Nested Loop)
Monotonic Stack (Most Optimal)

Approach 1: Brute Force
Intuition

For every day:

Look at every future day.
Stop when a warmer temperature is found.
Java
class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temperatures) {

        int n = temperatures.length;
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

                if (temperatures[j] > temperatures[i]) {
                    ans[i] = j - i;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}

